translation_en:
He is never born, and he never dies;  
having once been, he will never again cease to be.  
This one is unborn, eternal, everlasting, ancient;  
he is not slain when the body is slain.

This desire, this anger, born of rajas,  
is all-devouring and greatly sinful;  
know this here to be the enemy.

You are the imperishable supreme reality to be known;
You are the ultimate refuge of this universe.
You are the imperishable guardian of eternal dharma;
I regard You as the eternal Purusha.

Therefore arise and win renown;
conquer your enemies and enjoy a prosperous kingdom.
They have already been slain by me;
be only the instrument, O Savyasacin.

Obeisance to you from the front and from behind;  
obeisance to you on all sides, O all.  
You are of infinite power and immeasurable prowess;  
you pervade all, and so you are all.

Its form is not perceived here as such;
it has neither end nor beginning, nor any present basis.
Having cut down this deeply rooted ashvattha with the firm weapon of non-attachment,

I am seated in the heart of all beings;
from Me come memory, knowledge, and their loss.
I am indeed what is to be known through all the Vedas;
I am the maker of Vedanta and the knower of the Vedas.
